# PR review bot replies

Bot reply standard is defined inline in `git-pr-workflow-default.mdc` (section "Bot/reviewer reply standard").

Repo policy (**extended**): after **every** open PR — especially once CI is green and after **`npm run wait-for-bots`** — actively watch for and fully consider feedback from these reviewers:

| Priority | GitHub bot identity | Notes |
|----------|---------------------|--------|
| 1 | `sourcery-ai` | Often leaves overview + inline file threads |
| 2 | `gemini-code-assist` | File-level inline comments |
| 3 | `chatgpt-codex-connector` (Codex) | Inline severity badges / summaries |

**Sweep checklist (never rely only on Conversation summaries)**

1. `gh api repos/<owner>/<repo>/pulls/<n>/reviews` — capture reviews from all three above plus Copilot, CodeRabbit, etc.
2. `gh api repos/<owner>/<repo>/pulls/<n>/comments` — capture **every** inline thread for those bots (Gemini/Codex frequently attach comments here).
3. github.com **Files** tab — reopen threads grouped by path until none pending.

**Disposition bias**

- **Substantive** feedback from these bots (correctness, resilience, security, perf, clarity, hygiene): **implement by default** on the same PR branch when feasible; reply **in-thread** with **`implemented in <sha>`**.
- **Defer** only with a concrete reason (risk window, scope, dependency on another PR) + optional **`docs/REFACTOR_BACKLOG.md`** link; reply in-thread.
- **Decline** only with a concrete reason that cites repo constraints (`AGENTS.md`, compatibility, etc.); reply in-thread.

Do **not** merge while **any** substantive inline thread from Sourcery, Gemini, or Codex is unresolved **without** an explicit defer or decline reply.

Still applies to other bots (`copilot`, `coderabbit`, `greptile`, scanners): same reply standard.

Green **`ci_result`** does **not** replace thread closure.
